entry.summary: We establish $L^p$ Sobolev mapping properties for averages over certain curves in $\R^3$, which improve upon the estimates obtained by $L^2-L^\infty$ interpolation.

entry.title: Generalized Riemann - Liouville fractional derivatives for multifractal sets
entry.summary: The Riemann-Liouville fractional integrals and derivatives are generalized for cases when fractional exponent $d$ are functions of space and times coordinates (i.e. $d=d({\bf r}(t),t)$).

entry.title: An asymptotic expansion for a ratio of products of gamma functions
entry.summary: An asymptotic expansion of a ratio of products of gamma functions is derived. It generalizes a formula which was stated by Dingle, first proved by Paris, and recently reconsidered by Olver.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Internat. J. Math. & Math. Sci., Vol. 24, No. 8 (2000) 505-510

entry.title: Point-invariant classes of the third order ordinary differential equations
entry.summary: Point transformations of the 3-rd order ordinary differential equations are considered. Special classes of ordinary differential equations that are invariant under the general point transformations are constructed.

entry.title: Necessary and sufficient conditions for differentiability of a function of several variables
entry.summary: The necessary and sufficient conditions for differentiability of a function of several real variables stated and proved and its ramifications discussed.
entry.arxiv:comment: 5 pages; PSfile generated using MSword; corrected typos

entry.title: The spectral set conjecture and multiplicative properties of roots of polynomials
entry.summary: We obtain new partial results supporting the spectral set conjecture in dimension 1.

entry.title: Some light on Littlewood-Paley theory
entry.summary: The purpose of this note is to correct an error in a paper of M. Cowling, G. Fendler and J.J.F. Fournier, and to give a counterexample to a conjecture of J.-L. Rubio de Francia.
entry.arxiv:comment: 3 pages, no figures; submitted to Math Annalen

entry.title: Necessary and sufficient conditions for differentiating under the integral sign
entry.summary: We give necessary and sufficient conditions for differentiating under the integral sign an integral that depends on a parameter. The conditions require the equality of two iterated integrals and depend on being able to integrate every derivative. The Henstock integral is thus used in an essential way.

entry.title: Multiple Equilibria for an SIRS Epidemiological System
entry.summary: An SIRS type model of disease transmission in an open environment is discussed. We use the Poincar\'{e} index together with a perturbation method to show that the endemic proportions need not be unique.

entry.title: A proof of a multivariable elliptic summation formula conjectured by Warnaar
entry.summary: We prove a multivariable elliptic analogue of Jackson's 8W7 summation formula, which was recently conjectured by S.O.Warnaar.

entry.title: New bounds on Kakeya problems
entry.summary: We establish new estimates on the Minkowski and Hausdorff dimensions of Besicovitch sets and obtain new bounds on the Kakeya maximal operator.
entry.arxiv:comment: 24 pages, 5 figures, submitted, Journal d'Analyse de Jerusalem

entry.title: L'approximation par des polyn{√¥}mes {√†} coefficients entiers
entry.summary: This expository article proves some results of Ferguson, on the approximation of continuous functions on a compact subset of R by polynomials with integral coefficients.

entry.title: Remark on Periodic Solutions of Non Linear Oscillators
entry.summary: We contribute to the method of trigonometric series for solving differential equations of certain non linear oscillators. Key Words: series power solution, trigonometric series.
entry.arxiv:comment: 8 pages. To appear in Appl. Math.Letters

entry.title: Fuglede conjecture holds for convex planar domains
entry.summary: Let $\Omega$ be a compact convex domain in the plane. We prove that $L^2(\Omega)$ has an orthogonal basis of exponentials if and only if $\Omega$ tiles the plane by translation.

entry.title: Some sharp restriction theorems for homogeneous manifolds
entry.summary: We prove some restriction theorems for flat homogeneous surfaces of codimension greater than one.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Journal of Fourier Analysis and Applications, Volume 4 (1998), Number 1, pp. 105-128

entry.title: A sharp bilinear cone restriction estimate
entry.summary: The purpose of this paper is to prove an essentially sharp L^2 Fourier restriction estimate for light cones, of the type which is called bilinear in the recent literature.

entry.title: Representation of Infinitely Differentiable Functions by Dirichlet Series
entry.summary: The problem of representation of elements of weighted space of infinitely differentiable functions on real line by exponential series is considered.

entry.title: A weak-type orthogonality principle
entry.summary: We prove a weak-type estimate for a class of operators extending some of the almost orthogonality issues involved in the study of the bilinear Hilbert transform by Lacey and Thiele.

author.name: Jose Barrionuevo
author.arxiv:affiliation: University of South Alabama and Georgia Institute of Technology

author.name: Michael T. Lacey
author.arxiv:affiliation: University of South Alabama and Georgia Institute of Technology

entry.title: Divergent Cesaro and Riesz means of Jacobi and Laguerre expansions
entry.summary: We show that for $\delta$ below certain critical indices there are functions whose Jacobi or Laguerre expansions have almost everywhere divergent Cesaro and Riesz means of order $\delta$.

entry.title: On the $L^2$-norms of periodizations of functions
entry.summary: We prove that the $L^2([0,1]^d) \times SO(d))$ norm of periodizations of a function from $L^1(R^d)$ is equivalent to the $L^2(R^d)$ norm of the function itself in higher dimensions.

entry.title: A Note on Wiener-Hopf Determinants and the Borodin-Okounkov Identity
entry.summary: The continuous analogue of a Toeplitz determinant identity for Wiener-Hopf operators is proved. An example which arises from random matrix theory is studied and an error term for the asymptotics of the determinant is computed.

entry.title: A note on the Gurov-Reshetnyak condition
entry.summary: We established an equivalence between the Gurov-Reshetnyak and Muckenhoupt A_\infty conditions for an arbitrary absolutely continuous measures.

entry.title: A local smoothing estimate in higher dimensions
entry.summary: We prove the higher-dimensional analogue of Wolff's local smoothing estimate (Geom. Funct. Anal. 2001) for large p. As in the 2+1-dimensional case, the estimate is sharp for any given value of p, but it is likely that the range of p can be improved.

entry.title: Bounds for singular fractional integrals and related Fourier integral operators
entry.summary: We prove sharp L^p-L^q endpoint bounds for singular fractional integral operators and related Fourier integral operators, under the nonvanishing rotational curvature assumption.

entry.title: Singular Radon transforms and maximal functions under convexity assumptions
entry.summary: We prove variable coefficient versions of L^p boundedness results on Hilbert transforms and maximal functions along convex curves in the plane.
entry.arxiv:comment: 19 pages, to appear in Revista Matematica Iberoamericana

entry.title: Mean square discrepancy bounds for the number of lattice points in large convex bodies
entry.summary: We prove various estimates for the mean square lattice point discrepancy for dilates of a convex body.
entry.arxiv:comment: 18 pages, to appear in Journal d'Analyse Mathematiques

entry.title: Polynomial Solutions to Difference Equations Connected to Painleve' II-VI
entry.summary: Polynomials related to rational solutions of Painleve' equations satisfy certain difference equations. Conditions are given to acertain that all solutions really are polynomials.

entry.title: An introduction to Heisenberg groups
entry.summary: This is brief and hopefully friendly, with basic notions, a few different perspectives, and references with more information in various directions.
entry.arxiv:comment: Additional references and other modest adjustments

entry.title: Some remarks about homeomorphisms, "energy", and so on
entry.summary: This paper briefly discusses some questions with analytical and topological aspects, with hopefully some useful references on both sides.

entry.title: A nonterminating 8-phi-7 summation for the root system C_r
entry.summary: Using multiple q-integrals and a determinant evaluation, we establish a nonterminating 8-phi-7 summation for the root system C_r. We also give some important specializations explicitly.

entry.title: Some topics concerning analysis on metric spaces and semigroups of operators
entry.summary: This is a brief survey which reviews some traditional themes in harmonic analysis and some more recent areas of activity, connected to "analysis on fractals" in particular.
entry.arxiv:comment: to appear, Gazette des Mathematiciens, Societe Mathematique de France, and maybe even in French

entry.title: Some topics concerning integrals of derivatives and difference quotients on metric spaces
entry.summary: This article discusses several matters related to Sobolev, Poincare, and isoperimetric inequalities in various settings.
entry.arxiv:comment: submitted to the volume associated to the trimestre "Heat kernels, random walks, and analysis on manifolds and graphs" at the Centre Emile Borel, Institut Henri Poincare, Spring, 2002

entry.title: Estimates of functions with vanishing periodizations
entry.summary: We prove that if a function $f \in L^p({\Bbb {R}} ^d)$ has vanishing periodizations then $\|f\|_{p'} \lesssim \|f\|_{p}$, provided $1 \le p < \frac {2d}{d + 2}$ and dimension $d \ge 3$.

entry.title: The Uncertainty Principle for relatively dense sets and lacunary spectra
entry.summary: We obtain a new version of the Uncertainty Principle for functions with Fourier transforms supported on a lacunary set of intervals. This is a generalization of Zygmund's theorem on lacunary trigonometric series to the real line in the spirit of the Logvinenko-Sereda theorem for relatively dense sets.

entry.title: The amplitude modulation transform
entry.summary: Motivated by the study of the local extrema of sin(x)/x we define the \emph{Amplitude Modulation} transform of functions defined on (subsets of) the real line. We discuss certain properties of this transform and invert it in some easy cases.

entry.title: An inequality on Chebyshev polynomials
entry.summary: We define a class of multivariate Laurent polynomials closely related to Chebyshev polynomials, and prove the simple but somewhat surprising (in view of the fact that the signs of the coefficients of the Chebyshev polynomials themselves alternate) result that their coefficients are non-negative.

entry.title: Where the Buffalo Roam: Infinite Processes and Infinite Complexity
entry.summary: These informal notes, initially prepared a few years ago, look at various questions related to infinite processes in several parts of mathematics, with emphasis on examples.

entry.title: Darboux-Halphen-Brioshi system with rank four
entry.summary: We will determine the condition that a homogeneous quadratic equation with rank four becomes the Darboux-Halphen-Brioshi system in terms of the associated non-associative algebra.

entry.title: Harmonic measure and "locally flat" domains
entry.summary: We will review work with Tatiana Toro yielding a characterization of those domains for which the harmonic measure has a density whose logarithm has vanishing mean oscillation.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proceedings of the ICM, Beijing 2002, vol. 2, 701--710

entry.title: Falconer conjecture in the plane for random metrics
entry.summary: We prove the following variant of the Falconer conjecture in the plane. If the dimension of a compact planar set is greater than one, then the distance set with respect to almost every ellipse has positive Lebesgue measure.

entry.title: A Counterpart of Bessel's Inequality in Inner Product Spaces and Some Gruss Type Related Results
entry.summary: A counterpart of the famous Bessel's inequality for orthornormal families in real or complex inner product spaces is given. Applications for some Gruss type inequalities are also provided.

entry.title: An Inequality of Ostrowski Type via Pompeiu's Mean Value Theorem
entry.summary: An inequality providing some bounds for the integral mean via Pompeiu's mean value theorem and applications for quadrature rules and special means are given.

entry.title: On Bessel and Gruss Inequalities for Orthornormal Families in Inner Product Spaces
entry.summary: A new counterpart of Bessel's inequality for orthornormal families in real or complex inner product spaces is obtained. Applications for some Gruss type results are also provided.

entry.title: Some New Results Related to Bessel and Gruss Inequalities for Orthogonal Families in Inner Product Spaces
entry.summary: Some new counterparts of Bessel's inequality for orthornormal families in real or complex inner product spaces are pointed out. Applications for some Gruss type inequalities are also empahsized.

entry.title: A Generalisation of an Ostrowski Inequality in Inner Product Spaces
entry.summary: A generalisation of inner product spaces of an inequality due to Ostrowski and applications for sequences and integrals are given.

entry.title: A Counterpart of Schwarz's Inequality in Inner Product Spaces
entry.summary: A new counterpart of Schwarz's inequality in inner product spaces and applications for isotonic functionals, integrals and sequences are provided.

entry.title: Some Companions of Ostrowski's Inequality for Absolutely Continuous Functions and Applications
entry.summary: Companions of Ostrowski's integral ineqaulity for absolutely continuous functions and applications for composite quadrature rules and for p.d.f.'s are provided.

entry.title: Gruss Type Discrete Inequalities in Inner Product Spaces, Revisited
entry.summary: Some sharp inequalities of Gruss type for sequences of vectors in real or complex inner product spaces are obtained. Applications for Jensen's inequality for convex functions defined on such spaces are also provided.

entry.title: A Generalisation of the Cassels and Greub-Reinboldt Inequalities in Inner Product Spaces
entry.summary: A generalisation of the Cassels and Greub-Reinboldt inequalities in complex or real inner product spaces and applications for isotonic linear functionals, integrals and sequences are provided.

entry.title: Bounding the Cebysev Functional for Sequences of Vectors in Normed Linear Spaces
entry.summary: Some new bounds for Cebysev functional for sequences of vectors in normed linear spaces are pointed out.

entry.title: Some remarks about Cauchy integrals
entry.summary: This article describes some aspects of Cauchy integrals and related geometry of sets and measures in Euclidean spaces, etc.
entry.arxiv:comment: latex-2e, 29 pages. Some combinations and adjustments

entry.title: Contributions to the Theory of the Barnes Function
entry.summary: This paper presents a family of new integral representations and asymptotic series of the multiple gamma function. The numerical schemes for high-precision computation of the Barnes gamma function and Glaisher's constant are also discussed.

entry.title: On multidimensional F. Riesz's "Rising Sun" Lemma
entry.summary: A multidimensional version of the Riesz rising sun lemma is proved by means of a generalized dyadic process.

entry.title: Some notes about matrices, 2
entry.summary: Here we briefly discuss lattices in Euclidean spaces and spaces of lattices, which are basic objects that can be described in terms of matrices and are important settings in classical analysis.

entry.title: More About Trigonometric Series and Integration
entry.summary: In this paper the discussion of the effect of trigonometric series on the theory of integration is continued from an earlier paper by Gluchoff, Trigonometric series and theories of integration, Math.Mag., 67 (1994), 3--20.

entry.title: Some notes about matrices, 5
entry.summary: This short survey reviews some aspects of spaces of positive-definite self-adjoint linear transformations on R^n and on C^n, including the standard Riemannian metric and the relation with the exponential mapping acting on self-adjoint linear transformations, which indeed leads to geodesics of positive-definite linear transformations.

entry.title: Summation formulae for elliptic hypergeometric series
entry.summary: Several new identities for elliptic hypergeometric series are proved. Remarkably, some of these are elliptic analogues of identities for basic hypergeometric series that are balanced but not very-well-poised.

entry.title: The Schlesinger System and the Riemann-Hilbert Problem
entry.summary: We generalize some classical results for the Schlesinger system of partial differential equations and give the explicit form of its solution, associated with rational matrix functions in general position.

entry.title: Erzeugung nichtlinearer gew√∂hnlicher Differentialgleichungen mit vorgegebener Lie-Algebra von Punktsymmetrien [Generation of ordinary differential equations with predetermined Lie algebra of point symmetries]
entry.summary: For any $n\in\mathbb{N}$ a nonlinear ordinary differential equation with Lie algebra of point symmetries isomorphic to $\frak{sl}(2,\mathbb{R})$ is given.

entry.title: On the absolute N_{q_Œ±}-summability of rth derived conjugate series
entry.summary: The object of the present paper is to study the absolute $N_{q_{\alpha}}$-summability of $r$th derived conjugate series generalizing a known result.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proc. Indian Acad. Sci. (Math. Sci.), Vol. 113, No. 3, August 2003, pp. 223-241

entry.title: A Weyl type formula for Fourier spectra and frames
entry.summary: We prove qualitative and quantitative results concerning the asymptotic density in dilates of centered convex bodies of the frequency vectors of orthogonal exponential bases and frames associated to bounded domains in Euclidean space.

entry.title: Reverses of the Cauchy-Bunyakovsky-Schwarz Inequality for n-tuples of Complex Numbers
entry.summary: Some new reverses of the Cauchy-Bunyakovsky-Schwarz inequality for n-tuples of real and complex numbers related to Cassels and Shisha-Mond results are given.

entry.title: Another proof of Bailey's 6-psi-6 summation
entry.summary: Adapting a method used by Cauchy, Bailey, Slater, and more recently, the second author, we give a new proof of Bailey's celebrated 6-psi-6 summation formula.

entry.title: New bounds on the Hermite polynomials
entry.summary: We shall establish two-side explicit inequalities, which are asymptotically sharp up to a constant factor, on the maximum value of $|H_k(x)| e^{-x^2/2},$ on the real axis, where $H_k$ are the Hermite polynomials.

entry.title: Commutators of singular integrals on generalized $L^p$ spaces with variable exponent
entry.summary: A classical theorem of Coifman, Rochberg, and Weiss on commutators of singular integrals is extended to the case of generalized $L^p$ spaces with variable exponent.

entry.title: Sur les Theoremes I et II de Painleve
entry.summary: We lecture on fundamental Painleve's early Theorems on first order ordinary differential equations with many examples. We end-up with two conjectures about the global analytic continuation of holonomy maps locally defined by Theorem II.

entry.title: Infinite Product Representations fot Multiple Gamma Function
entry.summary: Two kinds of infinite product representations for Vign\'eras multiple gamma function are presented. As an application of these formulas, a multiplication formula for the function is derived.

entry.title: Necessary and sufficient condition of Morse-Sard theorem for real valued functions
entry.summary: Necessary and sufficient condition is given for a set $A\subset R^1$ to be a subset of the critical values set for a $C^k$ function $f:R^m \to R^1$.

entry.title: On modular inequalities in variable L^p spaces
entry.summary: We show that the Hardy-Littlewood maximal operator and a class of Calder\'on-Zygmund singular integrals satisfy the strong type modular inequality in variable $L^p$ spaces if and only if the variable exponent $p(x)\sim const$.

entry.title: On the algebraic solutions of the sixth Painlev√© equation related to second order Picard-Fuchs equations
entry.summary: We describe two algebraic solutions of the sixth Painlev\'e equation which are related to (isomonodromic) deformations of Picard-Fuchs equations of order two.

entry.title: Some remarks on another proof of geometrical Paley-Wiener theorems for the Dunkl transform
entry.summary: We argue that another proof by Trimeche of the geometrical form of the Paley-Wiener theorems for the Dunkl transform is not correct.

entry.title: A Series Expansion for Integral Powers of Arctangent
entry.summary: A new series expansion for the function (arctan(x)/x)^n is developed and some properties of the expansion coefficients are obtained.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Integral Transforms and Special Functions Volume 17, Issue 7, 2006

entry.title: Degenerate Gauss hypergeometric functions
entry.summary: This is a study of terminating and ill-defined Gauss hypergeometric functions. Corresponding hypergeometric equations have a degenerate set of of 24 Kummer's solutions. We describe those solutions and relations between them.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Kyushu Journal of Mathematics, Vol. 61 (2007), pg. 109-135

entry.title: Some notes on harmonic and holomorphic functions
entry.summary: These notes are concerned with harmonic and holomorphic functions on Euclidean spaces, using quaternions and Clifford algebras in higher dimensions. The main themes are weak solutions, the mean-value property, and subharmonicity.

entry.title: Notes on functions on the unit disk
entry.summary: In these notes we consider power series representations of functions on the unit disk in the complex plane which define harmonic and holomorphic functions and related matters concerning boundary values, Poisson kernels, and so on.

entry.title: Uniqueness of limit cycles for a class of planar vector fields
entry.summary: In this paper we give sufficient conditions to ensure uniqueness of limit cycles for a class of planar vector fields. We also exhibit a class of examples with exactly one limit cycle.

entry.title: Summation formulae for noncommutative hypergeometric series
entry.summary: We establish several summation formulae for hypergeometric and basic hypergeometric series involving noncommutative parameters and argument. These results were inspired by a recent paper of J. A. Tirao [Proc. Nat. Acad. Sci. 100 (14) (2003), 8138-8141].

entry.title: Flat chains in banach spaces
entry.summary: We generalize the notion of flat chains with arbitrary coefficient groups to Banach spaces and prove a sequential compactness result. We also remove the restriction that a flat chain have finite mass in order for its support to exist.

entry.title: Cosine products, Fourier transforms, and random sums
entry.summary: We investigate several infinite product of cosines and find the closed form using the Fourier transform. The answers provide limiting distributions for some elementary probability experiments.

entry.title: Integral representation of some functions related to the Gamma function
entry.summary: We prove that the functions Phi(x)=[Gamma(x+1)]^{1/x}(1+1/x)^x/x and log Phi(x) are Stieltjes transforms.

entry.title: Multi-parameter paraproducts
entry.summary: We prove that the classical Coifman-Meyer theorem holds on any polydisc $\T^d$ of arbitrary dimension $d\geq 1$.
entry.arxiv:comment: 13 pages, no figures, submitted, Revista Math

entry.title: Riesz transform and Riesz potentials for Dunkl transform
entry.summary: Analogous of Riesz potentials and Riesz transforms are defined and studied for the Dunkl transform associated with a family of weighted functions that are invariant under a reflection group. The $L^p$ boundedness of these operators is established in certain cases.

entry.title: Noncommutative extensions of Ramanujan's 1-psi-1 summation
entry.summary: Using functional equations, we derive noncommutative extensions of Ramanujan's 1-psi-1 summation.
entry.arxiv:comment: 9 pages, prepared with LaTeX using SIAM's siamltex style file, submitted to Proceeedings of IWOP'04, special volume of ETNA (Electronic Transactions on Numerical Analysis)

entry.title: An example on the maximal function associated to a nondoubling measure
entry.summary: We show that there is a measure $\mu$, defined on the hyperbolic plane and with polynomial growth, such that the centered maximal operator associated to $\mu$ does not satisfy weak type $(1,1)$ bounds.

entry.title: Hahn decomposition and Radon-Nikodym theorem with a parameter
entry.summary: The paper contains a simple proof of the classical Hahn decomposition theorem for charges and, as a corollary, an explicit measurable in parameter construction of a Radon-Nikodym derivative of one measure by another.

entry.title: Divided Differences
entry.summary: Starting with a novel definition of divided differences, this essay derives and discusses the basic properties of, and facts about, (univariate) divided differences.

entry.title: On Besicovitch Almost Periodic Selections of Multivalued Maps
entry.summary: We prove that Besicovitch almost periodic multivalued maps ${\bf R}\ni t \to F(t) \in cl U$ have Besicovitch almost periodic selections, where $cl U$ is the collection of non-empty closed sets of a complete metric space $U$.

entry.title: Some remarks on a paper by L. Carlitz
entry.summary: We study a family of orthogonal polynomials which generalizes a sequence of polynomials considered by L. Carlitz. We show that they are a special case of the Sheffer polynomials and point out some interesting connections with certain Sobolev orthogonal polynomials.

entry.title: Convex functions with unbounded gradient
entry.summary: We show that domains, that allow for convex functions with unbounded gradient at their boundary, are convex.

entry.title: An elliptic determinant transformation
entry.summary: We prove a transformation formula relating two determinants involving elliptic shifted factorials. Similar determinants have been applied to multiple elliptic hypergeometric series.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: in M. Noumi and K. Takasaki (eds.), "Elliptic Integrable Systems", Rokko Lectures in Math. 18, Kobe University, 2005, pp. 241-246

entry.title: Ramanujan's Inverse Elliptic Arc Approximation
entry.summary: We suggest a continued fraction origin to Ramanujan's approximation to {(a-b)/(a+b)}^2 in terms of the arc length of an ellipse with semiaxes a and b. Moreover, we discuss the asymptotic accuracy of the approximation.

entry.title: A family of Sobolev Orthogonal Polynomials on the Unit Ball
entry.summary: A family of orthonormal polynomials on the unit ball $B^d$ of $\RR^d$ with respect to the inner product $$ < f,g > = \int_{B^d}\Delta[(1-\|x\|^2) f(x)] \Delta[(1-\|x\|) g(x)] dx, $$ where $\Delta$ is the Laplace operator, is constructed explicitly.

entry.title: Generalizations of the Carleson-Hunt theorem I. The classical singularity case
entry.summary: In this article we prove L^p estimates for a general maximal operator, which extend both the classical Coifman-Meyer and Carleson-Hunt theorems in harmonic analysis

entry.title: Asymptotic analysis of the Askey-scheme II: from Charlier to Hermite
entry.summary: We analyze the Hermite polynomials $H_{n}(\xi)$ and their zeros asymptotically as $n\to\infty,$ using the limit relation between the Charlier and Hermite polynomials. Our formulas involve some special functions and they yield very accurate approximations.

entry.title: Some BMO estimates for vector-valued multilinear singular integral operators
entry.summary: In this paper, we prove some BMO end-point estimates for some vector-valued multilinear operators related to certain singular integral operators.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proc. Indian Acad. Sci. (Math. Sci.), Vol. 115, No. 2, May 2005, pp. 167-190

entry.title: Some observations on a Kapteyn series
entry.summary: We study the Kapteyn series $% %TCIMACRO{\dsum \limits_{n=1}^{\infty}}% %BeginExpansion {\displaystyle\sum\limits_{n=1}^{\infty}} %EndExpansion t^{n}\mathrm{J}_{n}(nz) $. We find a series representation in powers of $z$ and analyze its radius of convergence.

entry.title: A recursive bound for a Kakeya-type maximal operator
entry.summary: A (d,k) set is a subset of R^d containing a translate of every k-dimensional plane. Bourgain showed that for 2^{k-1}+k \geq d, every (d,k) set has positive Lebesgue measure. We give an L^p bound for the corresponding maximal operator.

entry.title: Absolutely continuous functions with values in metric spaces
entry.summary: We present a general theory of absolutely continuous paths with values in metric spaces using the notion of metric derivatives. Among other results, we prove analogues of the Banach-Zarecki and Vallee Poussin theorems.

entry.title: Asymptotic behavior of the unbounded solutions of some boundary layer equations
entry.summary: We give an asymptotic equivalent at infinity of the unbounded solutions of some boundary layer equations arising in fluid mechanics.

entry.title: Tauberian theorems for distributions in the Lizorkin spaces
entry.summary: In this paper some multidimensional Tauberian theorems for the Lizorkin distributions (without restriction on the support) are proved. Tauberian theorems of this type are connected with the Riesz fractional operators.

entry.title: The Grone Merris Conjecture and a quadratic eigenvalue problem
entry.summary: We verify the Grone Merris conjecture for a class of graphs. We do this by curve sketching in the sense of first year calculus. That is, we do it by homotopy methods.

entry.title: Riemann-Hilbert Methods in the Theory of Orthogonal Polynomials
entry.summary: In this paper we describe various applications of the Riemann-Hilbert method to the theory of orthogonal polynomials on the line and on the circle.

entry.title: Singular limits for 4-dimensional semilinear elliptic problems with exponential nonlinearity
entry.summary: Using some nonlinear domain decomposition method, we prove the existence of singular limits for solution of semilinear elliptic problems with exponential nonlinearity.

entry.title: A uniqueness result on boundary interpolation
entry.summary: Let $f$ be an analytic function mapping the unit disk $\D$ to itself. We give necessary and sufficient conditions on the local behavior of $f$ near a finite set of boundary points that requires $f$ to be a finite Blaschke product.

entry.title: Davies-Harrell Representations, Otelbaev's Inequalities
entry.summary: We find an asymptotics on the diagonal of the Green function of a Sturm-Liouville operator and give its applications for Riccati equation.
entry.arxiv:comment: 31 pages. The shortened version of this paper is to be submitted to Journal of Mathematical Analysis and Applications

entry.title: Parameter-based Fisher's information of orthogonal polynomials
entry.summary: The Fisher information of the classical orthogonal polynomials with respect to a parameter is introduced, its interest justified and its explicit expression for the Jacobi, Laguerre, Gegenbauer and Grosjean polynomials found.

entry.title: On A Relation Between $q$-Exponential And $Œ∏$-Function
entry.summary: We will use a discrete analogue of the classical Laplace method to show that for infinitely many positive integers $n$, the main term of the asymptotic expansion of the scaled $q$-exponential $(-q^{-nt+1/2}u;q)_{\infty}$ could be expressed in $\theta$-function.

entry.title: Existence of periodic solutions for the Lotka-Volterra type systems
entry.summary: In this paper we prove the existence of non-stationary periodic solutions of delay Lotka-Volterra equations. In the proofs we use the degree for $S^1$-equivariant maps.

entry.title: On Sums, Products, and the multidimensional Falconer problem
entry.summary: A set in d dimensional Euclidean space with d larger than 2 having Hausdorff dimension at least d/2 must have distance set with Hausdorff dimension strictly greater than 1/2.

entry.title: Fixed point theory for composite maps on almost dominating extension spaces
entry.summary: New fixed point results are presented for ${\cal U}_c^{\kappa}(X,X)$ maps in extension type spaces.

entry.title: Rigorous bounds of Stokes constants for some nonlinear ODEs at rank one irregular singularities
entry.summary: A rigorous way to obtain sharp bounds for Stokes constants is introduced and illustrated on a concrete problem arising in applications.

entry.title: An application of lambda-method on Shafer-Fink's inequality
entry.summary: In the paper $\lambda$-method Mitrinovic-Vasic is applied aiming to improve Fink's inequality, and Shafer's inequality for arcus sinus function is observed.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Univ. Beograd. Publ. Elektrotehn. Fak., Ser. Mat. 8 (1997), 90-92

entry.title: On Relations among Fourier Coefficients and Sum-functions
entry.summary: We generalize five theorems of Leindler on the relations among Fourier coefficients and sum-functions under the more general $NBV$ condition.
entry.arxiv:comment: 17 pages, Accepted by Studia Sci. Math. Hungar

entry.title: Exact solution of a nonlinear optimization problem
entry.summary: In this manuscript, we solve a nonlinear optimization problem in the study of maximizing cooling temperature using inhomogeneous thermoelectric materials.

entry.title: An Inequality for Basic Confluent Hypergeometric Series
entry.summary: In this very short note we will derive an inequality for a class of entire functions including all the confluent basic hypergeometric series and an inequality for a class of meromorphic functions including theta functions.

entry.title: One cannot hear the winding number
entry.summary: We construct an example of two continuous maps f and g of the circle to itself with the same absolute value of the Fourier transform but with different winding numbers, answering a question of Brezis.

entry.title: Mappings and spaces, 2
entry.summary: This paper is concerned with analysis on metric spaces in a variety of settings and with several kinds of structure.
entry.arxiv:comment: 34 pages, latex. additional references and a few other adjustments

entry.title: Two variable deformations of the Chebyshev measure
entry.summary: We construct one and two parameter deformations of the two dimensional Chebyshev polynomials with simple recurrence coefficients, following the algorithm in [3]. Using inverse scattering techniques, we compute the corresponding orthogonality measures.

entry.title: The Painlev√© transcendents with solvable monodromy
entry.summary: We will study special solutions of the fourth, fifth and sixth Painlev\'e equations with generic values of parameters whose linear monodromy can be calculated explicitly. We will show the relation between Umemura's classical solutions and our solutions.

entry.title: An elementary proof of the meromorphy of the integral of f^z for real-analytic f
entry.summary: A proof of a result of Atiyah and Bernstein/Gelfand concerning the title's topic is given that relies solely on the recent elementary resolution of singularities algorithm of the author.

entry.title: On the monotonicity of positive invariant harmonic functions in the unit ball
entry.summary: A monotonicity property of Harnack inequality is proved for positive invariant harmonic functions in the unit ball.

entry.title: Some algebraic notions related to analysis on metric spaces
entry.summary: There are versions of "calculus" in many settings, with various mixtures of algebra and analysis. In these informal notes we consider a few examples that suggest a lot of interesting questions.

entry.title: Discrete Ingham type inequalities with a weakened gap condition
entry.summary: We establish discrete Ingham type and Haraux type inequalities for exponential sums satisfying a weakened gap condition. They enable us to obtain discrete simultaneous observability theorems for systems of vibrating strings or beams.

entry.title: Remarks on the Zeros of the Associated Legendre Functions with Integral Degree
entry.summary: We present some formulas for the computation of the zeros of the integral-degree associated Legendre functions with respect to the order.

entry.title: Rational solutions of KZ equation, case $S_4$
entry.summary: We consider the Knizhnik-Zamolodchikov system of linear differential equations. The coefficients of this system are generated by elements of the symmetric group $S_n$. We separately investigate the case $S_4$. In this case we solve the corresponding KZ-equation in the explicit form.

entry.title: Note on the Schwarz Triangle functions
entry.summary: We shown the rationality of the Taylor coefficients of the inverse of the Schwarz triangle functions for a triangle group about any vertex of the fundamental domain.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Bulletin of the Australian Mathematical Society, 72 (2005), 385--389

entry.title: Affine Schwarz map for the hypergeometric differential equation
entry.summary: We propose an affine version of the Schwarz map for the hypergeometric differential equation, and study its image when the monodromy group is finite.

entry.title: Low regularity classes and entropy numbers
entry.summary: We note a sharp embedding of the Besov space $B^\infty_{0,q}(\bbT)$ into exponential classes and prove entropy estimates for the compact embedding of subclasses with logarithmic smoothness, considered by Kashin and Temlyakov.

entry.title: Numerical Evaluation of Generalized Hypergeometric Functions for Degenerated Values of Parameters
entry.summary: In this paper, we give an algorithm to generate connection formulas of generalized hypergeometric functions ${}_p F_{p-1}$ for degenerated values of parameters. We also show that these connection formulas give a fast method for numerical evaluation of generalized hypergeometric functions near $\infty$.

entry.title: On quasiplanes in Euclidean spaces
entry.summary: A variational inequality for the images of $k$-dimensional hyperplanes under quasiconformal maps of the $n$-dimensional Euclidean space is proved when $1\le k\le n-2 .$

entry.title: A few remarks about operator theory, topology, and analysis on metric spaces
entry.summary: Some basic facts about Fredholm indices are briefly reviewed, often used in connection with Toeplitz and pseudodifferential operators, and which may be relevant for operators associated to fractals.
entry.arxiv:comment: 5 pages, latex-2e. A few additions and adjustments

entry.title: Tube-measurability
entry.summary: Define an outer measure on R^n by taking the infimum, over all covers of the set by tubes, of the sum of the cross-sectional areas of the tubes. We show that the only measurable sets for this outer measure are its null sets and their complements.

entry.title: Iterated integral and the loop product
entry.summary: In this article we discuss a relation between the string topology and differential forms based on the theory of Chen's iterated integrals and the cyclic bar complex.

entry.title: A variation of Gronwall's lemma
entry.summary: We prove a variation of Gronwall's lemma.
entry.arxiv:comment: We corrected an error in the proof near equation (3)

entry.title: Multivariate Wavelet Frames
entry.summary: We proved that for any matrix dilation and for any positive integer $n$, there exists a compactly supported tight wavelet frame with approximation order $n$. Explicit methods for construction of dual and tight wavelet frames with a given number of vanishing moments are suggested.

entry.title: An analogue of Gutzmer's formula for Hermite expansions
entry.summary: We prove an analogue of Gutzmer's formula for Hermite expansions. As a consequence we obtain a new proof of a characterisation of the image of $ L^2(\R^n) $ under the Hermite semigroup. We also obtain some new orthogonality relations for complexified Hermite functions.

entry.title: On limit cycles appearing by polynomial perturbation of Darbouxian integrable systems
entry.summary: We prove an existential finiteness Varchenko-Khovanskii type result for integrals of rational 1-forms over the level curves of Darbouxian integrals.

entry.title: The integrals in Gradshteyn and Rhyzik. Part 2: Elementary logarithmic integrals
entry.summary: We describe methods to evaluate elementary logarithmic integrals. The integrand is the product of a rational function and a linear polynomial in ln x.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Scientia, Series A: Mathematical Sciences, Vol. 14 (2007), 7-15

entry.title: Existence and symmetry of minimizers for nonconvex radially symmetric variational problems
entry.summary: Nonconvex functionals with spherical symmetry are studied. Existence of one and radial symmetry of all global minimizers is shown with an approach based on convex relaxation.
entry.arxiv:comment: 22 pages, submitted to Calculus of Variations and Partial Differential Equations

entry.title: The integrals in Gradshteyn and Ryzhik. Part 4: The Gamma function
entry.summary: We present a systematic derivation of some definite integrals in the classical table of Gradshteyn and Ryzhik that can be reduced to the gamma function.

entry.title: On Asymptotics of $q$-Gamma Functions
entry.summary: In this paper we derive some asymptotic formulas for the $q$-Gamma function $\Gamma_{q}(z)$ for $q$ tending to 1.

entry.title: Necessary and sufficient conditions for solvability of the Hartman-Wintner problem for difference equations
entry.summary: For homogeneous difference equation of the second order we study the analogy of Hartman-Wintner problem on asymptotic integration of fundamental system of solutions as argument tends to infinity.

entry.title: Holonomic rank of A-hypergeometric differential-difference equations
entry.summary: We introduce A-hypergeometric differential-difference equation and prove that its holonomic rank is equal to the normalized volume of A with giving a set of convergent series solutions.

entry.title: Modified A-hypergeometric Systems
entry.summary: We will introduce a modified system of A-hypergeometric system (GKZ system) by applying a change of variables for Groebner deformations and study its Groebner basis and the indicial polynomials along the "exceptional hypersurface".

entry.title: Functions of q-positive type
entry.summary: In this paper we characterize the subspace of $\mathcal{L}_{q,1,v}$ of function which are the q-Bessel Fourier transform of positive functions in $\mathcal{L}_{q,1,v}$. As application we give a q-version of the Bochner's theorem.

entry.title: A formula for a quartic integral: a survey of old proofs and some new ones
entry.summary: We discuss several existing proofs of the value of a quartic integral and present a new proof that evolved from rational Landen transformations.

entry.title: The integrals in Gradshteyn and Ryzhik. Part 6: the beta function
entry.summary: We present the evaluation of definite integrals in the classical table by I. S. Gradshteyn and I. M. Ryzhik that can be reduced to the beta function.

entry.title: The integrals in Gradshteyn and Ryzhik. Part 7: Elementary examples
entry.summary: The classical table of integrals by I. S. Gradshteyn and I. M. Ryzhik contains some elementary integrals. We discuss their evaluations.

entry.title: Applications of the q-Fourier Analysis to the Symmetric Moment Problem
entry.summary: Sufficient condition for the symmetric moment problem to be determinate is given using standards methods of $q$-Fourier analysis. This condition it cannot be a particular case of Carleman's criterion.

entry.title: Landen survey
entry.summary: Landen transformations are maps on the coefficients of an integral that preserve its value. We present a brief survey of their appearnce in the literature.

entry.title: Trigonometric Series via Laplace Transforms
entry.summary: The author's method (math-ph/9804010) that uses the Laplace transform to find exact values for a large class of convergent series is extended to trigonometric series.
entry.arxiv:comment: Version close to the published one

entry.title: On the approximation by weighted ridge functions
entry.summary: We characterize the best $L_{2}$ approximation to a multivariate function by linear combinations of ridge functions multiplied by some fixed weight functions. In the special case when the weight functions are constants, we propose explicit formulas for both the best approximation and approximation error.

entry.title: Some Monotonicity Properties of Gamma and $q$-gamma Functions
entry.summary: We prove some properties of completely monotonic functions and apply them to obtain results on gamma and $q$-gamma functions.

entry.title: Some remarks about Clifford analysis and fractal sets
entry.summary: Although Clifford analysis is like complex analysis in many ways, there are obvious differences related to noncommutativity, and a few aspects of this are considered here.
entry.arxiv:comment: 5 pages, latex-2e. Some additions and other elaborations

entry.title: Polynomial Approximation and $œâ^r_œÜ(f,t)$ Twenty Years Later
entry.summary: About twenty years ago the measure of smoothness $\omega ^r_\phi (f,t)$ was introduced and related to the rate of polynomial approximation. In this article we survey developments about this and related concepts since that time.

entry.title: Uniform estimates for some paraproducts
entry.summary: We establish $L^p\times L^q$ to $L^r$ estimates for some paraproducts, which arise in the study of the bilinear Hilbert transform along curves.

entry.title: Transference of bilinear multiplier operators on Lorentz spaces
entry.summary: We prove a DeLeeuw type theorem of transference of boundedness for modulation invariant multiplier operators between the groups defined by the real line and the torus.

entry.title: On some properties of Riemann zeta function on critical line
entry.summary: The aim of this paper is to show further results following those published in [5], and to relate the Riemann zeta function to the relativistic cosmology.
entry.arxiv:comment: paper published in ACTA ARITHMETICA, XXVI (1974)

entry.title: Bilinear multipliers on Lorenzt spaces
entry.summary: We give one sufficient and two necessary conditions for boundedness between Lebesgue or Lorentz spaces of several classes of bilinear multiplier operators closely connected with the bilinear Hilbert transform.

entry.title: Muntz type Theorems I
entry.summary: In this paper, we concentrate our attention on the Muntz problem in the univariate setting and for the uniform norm.
entry.arxiv:comment: Paper accepted for publication in Surveys in Approximation Theory

entry.title: The Analytic Theory of Matrix Orthogonal Polynomials
entry.summary: We give a survey of the analytic theory of matrix orthogonal polynomials.

entry.title: An introduction to upper half plane polynomials
entry.summary: This is a straightforward introduction to the properties of polynomials in many variables that do not vanish in the open upper half plane. Such polynomials generalize many of the well-known properties of polynomials with all real roots.

entry.title: An algorithm for evaluating the Gamma function and ramifications
entry.summary: We provide a new algorithm for evaluating the gamma function at any (rational) point and a new infinite product representation free from the presence of Euler and Mascheroni constant.Formulae and inequalities seemingly new are obtained as byproducts of the method.

entry.title: The Walsh model for $M_2^{*}$ Carleson
entry.summary: We study the Walsh model of a certain maximal truncation of Carleson's operator, related to the Return Times Theorem from Ergodic Theory.

entry.title: A note on restricted X-ray transforms
entry.summary: We show how the techniques introduces by Christ can be employed to derive endpoint $L^p-L^q$ bounds for the X-ray transform associated to the line complex generated by the curve $t\to(t,t^2,...,t^{d-1}).$ Almost-sharp Lorentz space estimates are produced as well.

entry.title: Topics in Special Functions
entry.summary: The authors survey recent results in special functions, particularly the gamma function and the Gaussian hypergeometric function.

entry.title: Support of Non-separable Multivariate Scaling Function
entry.summary: We make an estimation of the support of a multivariable scaling function for an arbitrary dilation matrix. We give a method of calculating the values of the scaling function on a tight set using the knowledge of the size of the support.

entry.title: Rayleigh's Stretched String
entry.summary: We obtain rigorous a priori upper and lower bounds to the exact period of the celebrated Rayleigh stretched string differential equation.
entry.arxiv:comment: This paper has been withdrawn. There was an error in the proof of theorem 1
